This paper is about a popular policy search algorithm in Reinforcement Learning (RL), which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper discusses the convergence and optimization rates of the algorithm, which are topics typically studied in the subfield of optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control systems and regularized MDPs, which could potentially fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
